Vietnam has launched a support fund for victims of war-era defoliant, focusing on areas with high rates of birth defects and cancers.
The Red Cross initiated the fund, aiming to provide healing and reconstruction.
A federal judge ruled that the Veterans Administration must review benefit claims denied to Vietnam veterans due to exposure to Agent Orange.
Despite ongoing investigations, scientific evidence linking herbicides to conditions like diabetes remains inconclusive.
Vietnam is conducting a nation-wide census of Agent Orange victims, with more affected individuals found in central and northern provinces.
The effects of Agent Orange on humans and the environment continue to be a pressing concern.
